{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_78","type":"agent_message","text":"The remaining failure is not in `jandex` metadata anymore. `generateMetadata` shells out to a nested Gradle build and does not forward the active GraalVM as `org.gradle.java.home`, so the inner build still picks a different host JVM and its agent workers fail before metadata collection starts. I’m patching that handoff now so the user’s exact `generateMetadata` command can run against the intended GraalVM."}}
